Package ohos.utils

Class LightweightMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.utils.LightweightMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>

    public final class LightweightMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Map<K,V>
    Provides a container that implements the Map interfaces.

    The LightweightMap container uses less memory than the HashMap container, but may show poor performance when reaching a large size.

    It is recommended that you use this container when less memory is required.

    Note: The thread is secure only when data is read from the LightweightMap container.

    Since:
    1

      • put

        public V put​(K key,
             V value)
        Saves a key-value pair to an LightweightMap container.

        If the key of the key-value pair already exists in the LightweightMap container, the existing value of the key is overwritten by the new value.

        If the capacity of the LightweightMap container has been used up, it will be automatically expanded.

        Specified by:
        put in interface Map<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - Indicates the key of the key-value pair to be saved.
        value - Indicates the value of the key-value pair to be saved.

      • removeAt

        public V removeAt​(int index)
        Deletes a key-value pair at the location identified by index from an LightweightMap container.

        If index is a negative number, the key-value pair is located from the reverse direction.

        During the deletion, the system determines whether to expand or reduce capacity of the LightweightMap container. If the number of objects in the container is less than a specified number, the system reduces the capacity of the container.

        Parameters:
        index - Identifies the location of a key-value pair.
        Returns:
        Returns the key identified by index.
        Since:
        1
